        "16": {
            "text": "You pick up an ale glass and smash it across the edge of the table. The jagged\nglass is razor-sharp. As you draw it across the back of your left hand, a long\ncut appears trickling blood. Covering this wound with your right hand, you\nconcentrate and feel the warmth of your power as the wound heals. When you\nremove your right hand, no trace of the cut or any scar remains. The sailor\nstares at you in amazement.",
