        "20": {
            "text": "You follow this rat-infested street as it drops steeply to the wharves and\njetties of the River Dorn. From the edge of the waterfront, you see the Ragadorn\nBridge. It is the only crossing between the east and west sides of this sleazy\nport. Pushing your way through the crowds of people on the bridge, you enter a\nrubbish-strewn thoroughfare known as East Trade Lane.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 186.",
                    "section": "186"
                }
            ]
        },
        "21": {
            "text": "The trickster lies dead at your feet. Rolling him over with your foot, you\nremove several cards from the sleeves of his jacket and throw them on the table.\nThe crowd soon disperses and the tavern is a bustle of noise and activity once\nmore. The other card players retrieve their gold from the table and leave the\nremainder for you.\n\nTo find out how much has been left on the table, pick a number from the Random\nNumber Table. (In this instance, 0 = 10 instead of zero.) Now multiply this\nnumber by 3. The total is the number of Gold Crowns that are on the table. You\nmay also take the Card Sharp's Dagger if you wish. Remember to mark all the\nitems on your Action Chart.\n\nAs the body is being dragged outside, you walk to the bar and call for the\ninnkeeper. You press a Gold Crown into his hand and ask for a room for the\nnight.",
