        "29": {
            "text": "You release the lock and slide back the hatch cover. The sudden draught of air\ncauses flames to billow out of the hold. You stumble backwards, clutching your\nburnt face. Lose 2 ENDURANCE points.\n\n\"Fire! Fire!\" the cry goes up.\n\nIn panic the crew fight to put out the flames. It takes over an hour to control\nthe blaze. The damage is considerable-the entire store of food and fresh water\nwas in that hold, and the fire has completely ruined both, as well as weakened\nthe structure of the ship.\n\nAs you stand surveying the wreckage, the captain approaches you, his face\nblackened by the smoke. He is carrying something in a bundle under his arm. \"We\nmust talk in private, my lord,\" he says quietly.\n\nWithout replying, you turn and follow him below to his cabin.",
