        "163": {
            "text": "\"We've a full sail and a sharp prow. There's not a warship on the northern seas\nthat'll catch the Green Sceptre,\" says the captain.\n\nHe is proved right, for the pirate ship soon disappears over the horizon.\n\"Twenty-five years at sea and I've never known the Lakuri pirates to venture\nthis far north to raid,\" he says, stroking his beard thoughtfully. \"They must be\nafter a valuable cargo to sail so far from their tropical islands.\"\n\nAs the captain descends below deck to his cabin, you get an uneasy feeling that\nthe valuable cargo may be you.",
