                    "text": "Turn to 312.",
                    "section": "312"
                }
            ]
        },
        "220": {
            "text": "Searching the body, you discover all you need to prove that he was the assassin.\nInside his pockets, you find a half-empty vial of gnadurn sap, the deadly poison\nthat was used to taint your food. Then there is a scroll written in Giak, giving\ndetails of your expected arrival in Port Bax. He must have located you at\nRagadorn and hatched his murder plans there. You notice that the weapon he\ncarries is a Darklord blade, fashioned of black steel and forged in the furnaces\nof Helgedad, the infernal city of the Darklords beyond the Durncrag Range. Only\nthere in all of vast Magnamund can black steel be made. But the final proof of\nhis true identity is the serpent tattoo on his left wrist. The harbour thugs who\nattempted to kill you before you had even left Holmgard bore exactly the same\nmark.\n\nHis purse contains 23 Gold Crowns which you may keep. Do not forget to mark them\non your Action Chart.",
            "items": [
                {
                    "value": 23,
                    "name": "Gold Crowns",
                    "ac_section": "gold"
                }
            ],
            "choices": [
