        },
        "249": {
            "text": "During the course of the afternoon's journey, you chat with your fellow\ntravellers and learn about their backgrounds.\n\nhttp://www.projectaon.org/en/xhtml/lw/02fotw//ill15.png[Illustration]: You chat with your fellow travellers and learn about their\nbackgrounds.\n\nSitting opposite are two brothers named Ganon and Dorier. They are knights in\nthe Order of the White Mountain, warrior lords of Durenor who have pledged\nallegiance to protect the country from raids by the bandits of the Wildlands.\nThey own a castle and land near Port Bax. Next to them sits Halvorc the\nmerchant. His nose is swollen and his face is badly bruised thanks to Lachlan,\nthe Overlord of Ragadorn. A little misunderstanding about port taxes lost him\nhis cargo and most of his gold. Seated by the far door is a priest called\nParsion. Like you, he is a Sommlending who has journeyed across the Wildlands by\ncoach on his way to Port Bax. Beside you sits a young woman called Viveka. She\nis a mercenary adventuress who earns her gold by fighting for it, and sells her\nservices to the highest bidder. She is returning to Port Bax having collected\npayment for a successful adventure in Ragadorn.\n\nNot wishing to reveal your true identity, you have pretended to be a simple\npeasant. The travellers seem unaware of the war that now rages in Sommerlund.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 39.",
                    "section": "39"
                }
            ]
        },
        "250": {
            "text": "The soldier looks at you with a disbelieving stare.\n\n\"Where are your goods? Where is your horse or wagon? Merchants never travel to\nPort Bax on foot. You are no merchant-a bandit more like, desperate to put\ndistance between yourself and some foul deed best left untold. Go back to where\nyou have come from, scum. We have no need of the sort of goods you sell.\"\n\nIf you are to get past this border guard alive, you will have to come up with an\nalternative plan.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "words": [
                        "make",
                        "wide",
                        "detour",
                        "enter",
                        "forest",
                        "south",
                        [
                            "walk",
                            "away"
                        ],
                        "leave"
                    ],
                    "text": "If you wish to walk away, make a wide detour and enter the forest further south,\nturn to 244.",
                    "section": "244"
                },
                {
                    "text": "If you want to try to bribe the guard, turn to 68.",
                    "section": "68",
                    "words": [
                        "try",
                        "bribe",
                        "guard",
                        "offer",
                        "gold"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "words": [
                        "choose",
