                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        "251": {
            "text": "It is nearly dark when the small fishing boat passes through the harbour\nentrance of Ragadorn. You have still seen no sign of survivors from the storm\nand you fear the worst.\n\nYou notice that three of the fishermen are acting very suspiciously. They\nwhisper to each other and their eyes often glance at your money pouch. As the\nboat sails into the estuary of the River Dorn, they surround you and demand that\nyou hand over all your gold. You are about to fight them when an unexpected blow\nfrom behind knocks you to the deck. You see one of the fishermen raise his foot.\nAs it strikes your head, suddenly everything fades into darkness.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 194.",
                    "section": "194"
                }
            ]
        },
        "252": {
            "text": "You try to remember some of the stories told to you by an old Kai master called\nWise Hawk. He was envoy to Port Bax for many years, and he knew and loved this\ncity as well as any native Durenese. You recall him saying that the consulate\noverlooked Alin Square in the naval quadrant of the city. There is a sign to\nyour left pointing along the avenue.\n\n                            Naval Quadrant-1/2 Mile\n\nCertain this is the right direction, you walk confidently along the tree-lined\navenue.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 191.",
                    "section": "191"
                }
            ]
        },
        "253": {
            "text": "This street follows the harbour wall towards the River Dorn where it then turns\nsouth into Booty Walk. As you pass the warehouses lining the waterfront, you\nrecognize the stone signpost in the centre of the square ahead.",
            "alternate_choices": true,
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to continue south, turn to 303.",
                    "section": "303",
                    "words": [
                        "continue",
                        "south"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to walk along Barnacle Street and return to the tavern, turn to 177.",
                    "section": "177",
                    "words": [
                        "walk",
                        "barnacle",
                        "street",
                        "return",
                        "tavern"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "254": {
            "text": "For three days and nights you have followed the highway to the capital as it\nruns parallel to the River Durenon. The river valley is a wide belt of rich,\ncultivated land that climbs towards the Hammerdal Mountains, one of the highest\nranges in all of Magnamund.\n\nIt is on the morning of the fourteenth day of your quest, when six cloaked men\nappear at the edge of your camp. Lord-lieutenant Rhygar is the first to draw his\nsword. With a voice of authority he demands an explanation for their intrusion.\nIn reply, they unsheathe black swords. Rhygar shouts to his men to prepare for\ncombat as the cloaked strangers advance towards you.",
            "alternate_choices": true,
            "trim_choices": true,
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "If you have the Kai Discipline of Sixth Sense, turn to 344.",
                    "section": "344",
                    "requires": {
                        "kai_disciplines": "Sixth Sense"
                    },
                    "words": [
                        "kai",
                        "discipline",
                        "sixth",
                        "sense"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to draw your weapon and prepare to fight, turn to 69.",
                    "section": "69",
                    "requires_not": {
                        "kai_disciplines": "Sixth Sense"
                    },
                    "words": [
                        "draw",
