        "259": {
            "text": "Through the pouring rain, you can make out the dark shape of a city patrol\nmarching towards you. Rather than risk being stopped and possibly arrested, you\ndash into a nearby shop.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 161.",
                    "section": "161"
                }
            ]
        },
        "260": {
            "text": "The captain orders the ship to go alongside and pick up the three men. They are\nfishermen from the Sommerlund port of Tyso. Their boat was attacked last night\nby pirates, and they are the only survivors.\n\nYou give them food and warm clothing and they can barely hold back their tears\nof gratitude. As you prepare to continue your journey to Durenor, one of the men\noffers you a fine Sword as a token of his thanks. If you wish to accept this\ngift, remember to mark it on your Action Chart.",
            "items": [
                {
                    "name": "Sword",
                    "ac_section": "weapons"
                }
            ],
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 240.",
                    "section": "240"
                }
            ]
        },
        "261": {
            "text": "The road follows a course along a high, grassy ridge for many miles before\nturning northwards to the coast. You pass a village where the houses curve in a\ncircle around a large pond of stagnant water. As you ride through, a gaggle of\nSzall children come running towards you, shouting and throwing stones.\n\nYou descend into the deep valley beyond and gradually the moor gives way to\nricher land that has been cleared and ploughed. The hillside opposite is heavily\nwooded. You are not far from the coast and you can see the tall cliffs with\ntheir multicoloured bands of rock jutting out into the ocean.\n\nThen just as you are passing through a small copse, you hear desperate cries for\nhelp off to your right.",
            "alternate_choices": true,
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to aid the people in trouble, turn to 95.",
                    "section": "95",
                    "words": [
                        "aid",
                        "people",
                        "trouble",
                        "look",
                        "go"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to ignore their desperate pleas, continue riding along the road by\nturning to 198.",
                    "section": "198",
                    "words": [
                        "ignore",
                        "desperate",
                        "pleas",
                        "continue",
                        "riding",
                        "road"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "262": {
            "text": "The guard roughly pushes you aside and runs out of the watchtower towards Tomb\nSquare. There is a small room off the staircase and you decide to enter and\nsearch it before he returns. In it you discover:\n\n* Sword\n\n* Mace\n\n* Quarterstaff\n\n* Enough Food for 1 Meal\n\n* 6 Gold Crowns\n\n* Potion of Orange Liquid\n\nIf you wish to take any of these items, mark them on your Action Chart.\n\nAs you are leaving, you collide with another guard and you both tumble down the\nstairs, but before he can gather his senses, you have sprinted off into the\nnight.",
            "items": [
                {
                    "name": "Sword",
                    "ac_section": "weapons"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mace",
                    "ac_section": "weapons"
