        "263": {
            "text": "The man stares at the Seal with a look of shocked dismay. Without saying a word,\nhe gets up from his chair and beckons you to follow him up a flight of spiral\nstairs that lead to a domed chamber. Here you meet the captain of the port\nwatch. He listens intently as you tell of the war in Sommerlund and of your\nurgent mission.\n\n\"Issue a red pass immediately,\" he orders. \"Top priority.\"\n\nYou collect your Red Pass, leave the port watchtower, and hurry along the street\ntowards the harbour guards. (Mark the Red Pass on your Action Chart as a Special\nItem.)",
            "items": [
                {
                    "auto": true,
                    "name": "Red Pass",
                    "ac_section": "special_items"
                }
            ],
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 246.",
                    "section": "246"
                }
            ]
        },
        "264": {
            "text": "Focusing your powers of concentration on the snake's head, you will it to\nslither away in search of food. Slowly but surely your psychic suggestion works,\nand the snake eventually uncoils itself and vanishes into the long grass.\nBreathing a sigh of relief, you decide it would be safer to climb the tree and\nspend the rest of the night above the ground.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 312.",
                    "section": "312"
                }
            ]
        },
        "265": {
            "text": "At dusk on the tenth day of your quest, you experience your first sight of the\nmagnificent city of Port Bax. Like a diamond set in the green velvet shore, the\ntowers of the city glimmer in the pale light of a waxing moon. To the north is\nthe harbour and the formidable war fleet of the Durenese navy. To the east,\nbeyond the moss-covered city wall, stretches the Forest of Durenor. And there,\non the crest of a hill, stands a castle tall and proud, the crowning glory of\nthis beautiful port.\n\nYou enter Port Bax through an unguarded gate in the green city wall, and make\nyour way through the darkening streets towards the harbour.\n\nAs you turn into a tree-lined avenue, you notice the wide stone steps of a domed\nbuilding to your right. You stop to read the brass plaque.\n\n                                   CITY HALL\n\nDespite the late hour, the main doors are open.",
            "alternate_choices": true,
            "trim_choices": true,
            "choices": [
