        "284": {
            "must_eat": true,
            "text": "Cautiously, the soldiers surround you and take your Weapons and Backpack. (You\ndo not need to adjust your Action Chart.) The knight steps forward and raises\nthe visor of his helm.\n\n\"Who are you? What is your purpose in Tarnalin?\" he demands in a gruff voice.\n\nhttp://www.projectaon.org/en/xhtml/lw/02fotw//ill17.png[Illustration]: The knight is Lord Axim of Ryme, commander of King Alin's personal\nbodyguard.\n\nYou tell him that you are a Kai Lord from Sommerlund on an urgent mission to\nKing Alin. He seems unconvinced by your words until you show him the Seal of\nHammerdal. Then, without hesitation, he orders his men to return your belongings\nand ushers you through the wall of wagons. Beyond, you can see a horse-drawn\ncarriage waiting in the centre of the crowded tunnel.\n\n\"Back to Hammerdal without delay,\" he orders the driver, and you are thrown back\nin your seat as the coach moves off at breakneck speed.\n\nYou soon learn that the knight is Lord Axim of Ryme, commander of King Alin's\npersonal bodyguard. He was on his way to Port Bax when the Helghast entered\nTarnalin. He and ten soldiers were the only ones to survive a deadly encounter\nwith these evil creatures.\n\nDuring your ride through the Tarnalin, you must eat a Meal or lose 3 ENDURANCE\npoints. The journey to the capital will take five hours and you are advised by\nLord Axim to get some rest. As you slowly drift off to sleep, you begin a dream\nabout the Sommerswerd. You picture a triumphant return to Holmgard and the\ndefeat of the Darklord siege. Perhaps it will be a good omen of events to come?",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 9.",
                    "section": "9"
                }
            ]
        },
        "285": {
            "text": "You feel the snake's fangs catch in the arm of your tunic, but that is all. You\nare lucky that the only damage done was to your clothing. As the serpent\ndisappears into the long grass, you quickly climb the tree and spend the rest of\nthe night safely above the ground.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 312.",
                    "section": "312"
                }
            ]
        },
        "286": {
            "text": "You hit the water and swim submerged for over a minute to avoid the falling\nbodies and burning debris of the battle. When you are finally forced to the\nsurface for air, you catch a glimpse of a sight that raises your hopes of\nfulfilling your quest.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 109.",
                    "section": "109"
                }
            ]
        },
        "287": {
            "text": "You focus your concentration on the small, brass lock. After a few seconds, you\nhear a faint click that tells you that the inner latch is now unlocked. Inside\nis a scroll bearing the royal seal of Sommerlund and containing confidential\norders about your mission to Durenor. As you put the box back into its hiding\nplace, you notice that a deadly trap had been hidden in the lid. Your Kai\nDiscipline has saved you from the swift death of a poison needle. Closing the\ndrawers, you quickly check that nothing looks as though it has been disturbed\nbefore joining the captain on deck.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 175.",
                    "section": "175"
                }
            ]
        },
        "288": {
            "text": "Without uttering a word, the knight points to the woods behind you and returns\nto the watchtower. He disappears inside and bolts the door.\n\nThe forest here is very thick and the undergrowth is a tangle of weeds and\nbriars. It will be impossible to enter the wood on horseback. You realize you\nwill have to abandon your mount and continue on foot.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 244.",
                    "section": "244"
                }
            ]
        },
        "289": {
            "text": "You are welcomed by an old woman dressed from head to toe in white. She smiles\nand offers you a delicious cup of jala. Your experience of Ragadorn so far makes\nyou suspicious of the dark liquid and you politely refuse her offer. As you push\nthe steaming mug away, she notices the Seal on your finger.\n\n\"What a magnificent ring! Is it for sale?\" she asks, her eyes lighting up with\nexcitement. You tell her firmly that it is not but she will not accept your\nrefusal. She offers you any choice of the hundreds of potions that fill the\nglass cabinets behind her counter. As you turn to leave, she offers you 40 Gold\nCrowns.",
            "alternate_choices": true,
            "trim_choices": true,
            "is_special": true,
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to accept her offer, turn to 165.",
                    "section": "165",
                    "requires": {
                        "special_items": "Seal of Hammerdal"
                    },
                    "words": [
                        "accept",
                        "offer"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "text": "If you wish to leave the shop, turn to 186.",
                    "section": "186",
                    "words": [
                        "leave",
                        "shop",
                        "refuse"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "290": {
            "text": "The food smells delicious, but you notice that there are two or three drops of\nclear liquid on the side of the plate and another on the tray. At first you\nsuspect that it is only water, until you touch the fluid and notice that it is\nsticky. You recognize it as sap from the gnadurn tree, a deadly poison used by\nassassins because of its lack of flavour or scent. The shock of your discovery\nsoon turns to anger and you race out of the room, intent on discovering the\nidentity of your enemy.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 200.",
                    "section": "200"
                }
            ]
        },
        "291": {
            "text": "The forest here is extremely dense and the undergrowth is a tangle of bushy\nweeds. You ride for a mile in either direction and discover no track or path\nnear the watchtower. If you are to reach Port Bax you must dismount and enter\nthe forest on foot.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 244.",
                    "section": "244"
                }
            ]
        },
        "292": {
            "text": "You have been walking in the rain for over three hours when you are confronted\nby seven horsemen. They are mercenaries employed by the Overlord of Ragadorn and\nthey bear his emblem, a black ship on a red crest, upon their shields.\n\nThey demand that you hand over all your gold or they will kill you. When they\ndiscover that you have no gold, they chase you and eventually cut you down with\ntheir longswords. As you lie dying on the road, the last sight that you remember\nis the outline of Ragadorn on the distant horizon.",
            "choices": []
        },
        "293": {
            "text": "This road eventually ends at a deserted forest cabin. Although it is furnished,\na layer of fine dust covers everything inside and indicates that this place has\nnot been used for several months. It is a dead end, and you have wasted precious\ntime. You must return to the fork and take the left path without further delay.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 155.",
                    "section": "155"
                }
            ]
        },
        "294": {
            "text": "As you wrap the injured man in a large blanket, he drifts off into a sleep from\nwhich he will never awake. Back on deck, the bodies of the dead crew have been\nlaid together.\n\nCaptain Kelman approaches and hands you a vicious-looking blade. \"This is no\npirate sword, Lone Wolf. This weapon was forged in the furnaces of Helgedad. It\nis a Darklord blade.\"\n\nYou cast the evil sword into the sea where it quickly sinks beneath the waves,\nand return to the Green Sceptre. As the crew make ready to set sail for the\neast, you watch with sorrow as the Durenese trader sinks beneath the waves.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 240.",
                    "section": "240"
                }
            ]
        },
        "295": {
            "text": "A creature, much larger than the others and dressed in a magnificent robe of\npatchwork silk, screams an order in their strange language. All of the furry\ncreatures arm themselves with spears and swords that look as if they have been\ncrafted from broken wagon spokes and broom handles. With a strange battle-cry\nthat sounds like \"Gashgiss-Nashgiss\", they charge towards you. Your curiosity\nsoon gives way to the realization that you must evade them or be trampled to\ndeath by the sheer weight of their numbers.\n\nYou turn and sprint along the narrow corridor until their angry cries begin to\nfade. You reach the entrance to where the passage connects with the main tunnel,\nand continue your journey from there.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 340.",
                    "section": "340"
                }
            ]
        },
        "296": {
            "text": "The people flee the tavern as the town guard attack. There are six of them and\nyou must fight them one at a time.\n\nTown Guard Sergeant: COMBAT SKILL 13, ENDURANCE 22\n\nTown Guard Corporal: COMBAT SKILL 13, ENDURANCE 22\n\nTown Guard 1: COMBAT SKILL 13, ENDURANCE 22\n\nTown Guard 2: COMBAT SKILL 13, ENDURANCE 22\n\nTown Guard 3: COMBAT SKILL 13, ENDURANCE 22\n\nTown Guard 4: COMBAT SKILL 13, ENDURANCE 22",
