            ]
        },
        "309": {
            "text": "As you advance along the deck, the hideous creatures turn and flee from the\ngolden light of your sword. You notice something strange about this death-hulk,\nsomething familiar, but you are not quite sure what it is. Suddenly, a ghastly\nvoice behind you cries out your name.\n\nYou raise the Sommerswerd and spin around to face the voice. The sight that\nconfronts you fills your senses with a mortal terror.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 26.",
                    "section": "26"
                }
            ]
        },
        "310": {
            "text": "You soon reach the end of Oxyoke Way where it is crossed by another street\nrunning north to south. It is now so dark that you are unable to read the street\nsigns. You must find shelter for the night. To your right you see a light above\na sign.\n\n                       Ragadorn Stables and Coach Station\n\nUnder cover of the dark, you enter by a side entrance and spend the night safely\nhidden in the hay-loft.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 32.",
                    "section": "32"
                }
            ]
        },
        "311": {
            "text": "You come to rest face downwards in a tangle of thick bracken. The ringing of\nsteel and the horrible cries of the Helghast echo through the trees around you.\nYou are stunned and cannot move until a hand grabs your arm and pulls you\nupright. It is Rhygar. His face is bloodied and his armour is battered and\ncharred.\n\n\"We must flee these demons, Lone Wolf. Strength and steel will not avail us\nhere.\"\n\nYou glimpse the silhouette of six Helghast on the forest road above. Their minds\nbent on the slaughter of Rhygar's men, they fail to see you both slip away under\ncover of the wooded hillside.",
            "choices": [
                {
                    "text": "Turn to 299.",
                    "section": "299"
                }
            ]
        },
        "312": {
            "text": "Although you awake to a cold and rain-swept dawn, the branches of the tree and\nyour Kai cloak have kept you warm and dry during the night. Looking along the\ncoast road, in the distance you can see a wagon heading towards you.",
