        "325": {
            "text": "You sense that the left tunnel is the quickest route to Hammerdal by about two\nmiles. Just before you reach the junction you come across a large puddle in the\ncentre of the highway. You notice that two sets of footprints, about the size\nand shape of a man's boot trail away from the water and lead off into both\ntunnels. The prints are still wet and you judge that they were made within the\nlast twenty minutes.",
