        "341": {
            "text": "Shattered beams and torn sails are all that remain of the unfortunate merchant\nship. You ask the captain to search for survivors but he ignores your plea and\norders the crew to continue their duties. As the wreckage gradually disappears\nfrom view, the nagging fear that a similar fate could await you makes your\nthroat dry. You descend below deck and take care to lock the cabin door behind\nyou.",
